---
import CtaPanel from '../components/CtaPanel.astro';
import IconCard from '../components/IconCard.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../components/SectionHeader.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Consulting"
  description="Consulting, workshops and AI use analysis for organizations."
>
  <section class="page-shell service-shell">
    <header class="page-header service-hero">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Consulting</p>
        <h1>AI use analysis for organizations</h1>
      </div>
      <p>
        Consulting, workshops and human-AI work principles for teams that want to use AI
        more deliberately.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section aria-labelledby="services-title">
      <SectionHeader kicker="Services" title="What I help with" id="services-title">
        I offer practical, research-informed support for teams that need shared
        principles, verification habits and clearer human-AI workflows.
      </SectionHeader>
      <div class="service-card-grid">
        <IconCard icon="decision" title="AI use analysis">
          I help map how teams currently use AI and where support is realistic.
        </IconCard>
        <IconCard icon="concept" title="Process mapping">
          I map tasks, information flow, handoffs and points where AI enters work.
        </IconCard>
        <IconCard icon="work" title="Human-AI work model">
          I help design practical flows for what AI supports and what people own.
        </IconCard>
        <IconCard icon="trust" title="Team principles">
          I help teams create simple rules for trust, verification, data awareness and responsibility.
        </IconCard>
        <IconCard icon="article" title="AI literacy">
          I build a common language for using generative tools without hype.
        </IconCard>
        <IconCard icon="dialogue" title="Workshops and talks">
          I run briefings, workshops and lectures on AI, cyberpsychology and Human-AI Interaction.
        </IconCard>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="situations-title">
      <SectionHeader kicker="Typical situations" title="When this work is useful" id="situations-title">
        The problem is often not a lack of prompts. It is unclear judgment, unclear
        responsibility and inconsistent use across a team.
      </SectionHeader>
      <ul class="scenario-list scenario-grid">
        <li>A team uses AI, but everyone uses it differently.</li>
        <li>The organization wants to use AI, but has no shared principles.</li>
        <li>People paste sensitive information into tools without thinking through the risk.</li>
        <li>AI speeds up writing, but responsibility for the final output is unclear.</li>
        <li>Leaders do not know which tasks can be supported by AI.</li>
        <li>The organization wants practical internal AI use principles.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="process-title">
      <SectionHeader kicker="Process" title="How the collaboration can work" id="process-title">
        The format can stay compact, but I connect AI literacy with real tasks,
        risks and decision points.
      </SectionHeader>
      <ol class="process-list process-steps">
        <li>
          <strong>Discovery</strong>
          <p>where AI appears now and what the team needs to clarify</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Process map</strong>
          <p>which stages can be supported by AI and where handoffs happen</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Risks and responsibility</strong>
          <p>what requires verification, data awareness, control or another person</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Human-AI work model</strong>
          <p>what a sensible flow can look like in everyday work</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Principles and next steps</strong>
          <p>what to test, describe or clarify next</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="panel consulting-outcome" aria-labelledby="outcome-title">
      <p class="section-kicker">Outcome</p>
      <h2 id="outcome-title">What you can leave with</h2>
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>a map of current AI use in the team</li>
        <li>a list of processes where AI can support work</li>
        <li>areas that require caution, sources or another person</li>
        <li>simple principles for team AI use</li>
        <li>recommendations for verifying model outputs</li>
        <li>workshop notes or a short internal briefing for leaders or the team</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="panel consulting-note" aria-labelledby="not-title">
      <h2 id="not-title">What this is not</h2>
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>not legal advice</li>
        <li>not clinical advice</li>
        <li>not a promise of business outcomes</li>
        <li>not technical deployment work</li>
        <li>not shortcut-based prompt training</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <CtaPanel kicker="Contact" title="Talk about AI use in your organization." href="/contact/" linkLabel="Contact">
      Send a short note about the team, the current AI use and the kind of support you are looking for.
    </CtaPanel>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
